            <outline text="Stefan">
                <outline text="Key Idea #slide ">
                    <outline text="In an Indistinguishability under Chosen Plaintext Attack (IND-CPA) secure encryption scheme, ciphertexts reveal no information about the underlying plaintext to the adversary."/>
                    <outline text="This holds even if they can choose plaintexts and observe their corresponding ciphertexts. "/>
                    <outline text="This ensures that the encryption is indistinguishable under chosen plaintext attacks. "/>
                    <outline text="This definition can be extended to stronger settings, such as indistinguishability under chosen ciphertext attack (IND-CCA), where the adversary can also interact with a decryption oracle."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Indistinguishability under Chosen Plaintext Attack (IND-CPA) #slide ">
                    <outline text="The security of encryption based on indistinguishability can be defined based on a game between a challenger and an adversary. "/>
                    <outline text="There are various attack models to consider, this is Indistinguishability under Chosen Plaintext Attack (IND-CPA)."/>
                    <outline text="We define the security of an encryption scheme using the game defined as follows."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Setup #slide ">
                    <outline text="The encryption scheme is defined as a tuple of algorithms $$(\text{KeyGen}, \text{Enc}, \text{Dec})$$, where:">
                        <outline text="$$\text{KeyGen}$$: Generates a secret key $$ k $$."/>
                        <outline text="$$\text{Enc}(k, m)$$: Encrypts a plaintext $$ m $$ using the key $$ k $$, producing ciphertext $$ c $$."/>
                        <outline text="$$\text{Dec}(k, c)$$: Decrypts ciphertext $$ c $$ using $$ k $$ to recover $$ m $$."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="The adversary knows the encryption algorithm but does not know the secret key $$ k $$."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Challenge Phase #slide ">
                    <outline text="The adversary selects two plaintext messages, $$ m_0 $$ and $$ m_1 $$, of equal length."/>
                    <outline text="The challenger randomly selects a bit $$ b \in \{0, 1\} $$ and encrypts $$ m_b $$ using the secret key $$ k $$, producing the ciphertext $$ c^* = \text{Enc}(k, m_b) $$."/>
                    <outline text="The adversary is given the ciphertext $$ c^* $$."/>
                    <outline text="The adversary must guess the value of $$ b $$, determining whether the ciphertext corresponds to $$ m_0 $$ or $$ m_1 $$."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Security Definition #slide ">
                    <outline text="The encryption scheme is IND-CPA secure if the adversary has only a negligible advantage over random guessing. "/>
                    <outline text="Formally, the adversary’s advantage is defined as:">
                        <outline text="$$\text{Adv}_{\text{IND-CPA}} = \left| P(\text{guess } b = b^*)    - \frac{1}{2} \right|$$"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="where $$ P(\text{guess } b = b^*) $$ is the probability that the adversary correctly guesses $$ b $$, and $$ b^* $$ is the actual bit chosen."/>
                </outline>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Polycyclic Form Paper">
                <outline text="Algorithms">
                    <outline text="**algorithm** shifted_Hessenberg_form($$S,p$$)">
                        <outline text="$$v$$ := random vector in $$F_p^n$$;"/>
                        <outline text="$$w[1] := v$$;"/>
                        <outline text="$$j$$ := 1;"/>
                        <outline text="block_size[j] := 1;"/>
                        <outline text="**for ** i **from** $$2$$ to $$n$$ **do**">
                            <outline text="$$v'$$ := $$Sw[i]$$;"/>
                            <outline text="**if** $$v' \not \in \langle w[1],\ldots,w[i-1]\rangle$$ **then**  ">
<outline text="$$w[i] := v'$$;"/>
<outline text="$$v$$ := $$Sv'$$;"/>
<outline text="block_size[j] := block_size[j]+1;"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="**else**">
<outline text="$$w[i]$$ := random vector $$\not\in \langle w[1],\ldots,w[i-1]\rangle$$;"/>
<outline text="$$j$$ := $$j+1$$;"/>
<outline text="block_size[j] := 1;"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="**fi**; "/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**od**;"/>
                        <outline text="**return**(block_size, $$[V | v]$$);"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="**end**;"/>
                    <outline text="**algorithm** block_cyclic_form($$S$$)">
                        <outline text="$$(\tilde{C}, blocks)$$ := polycyclic_form($$S$$);"/>
                        <outline text="$$l := length(blocks)$$;"/>
                        <outline text="**for ** i **from** $$2$$ to $$l$$ **do**">
                            <outline text="\\\ Eliminate all non-zero entries in current block bottom row, to make block diagonal "/>
                            <outline text="**for ** j **from** $$1$$ to $$blocks[i]-1$$ **do**">
<outline text="\\\ Elimate $$s_{b\_s[i],j}$$"/>
<outline text="$$C$$ := RowColumnOp(C, i, j); "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="**od**;"/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="**od**;"/>
                        <outline text="**return** $$V | \,[v]$$;"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="**end**;"/>
                </outline>
